katzenthal.title: Katzenthal
katzenthal.description: Katzenthal is a commune in the Haut-Rhin department in Alsace in north-eastern France.

grand-ballon.title: Grand Ballon
grand-ballon.description: Le Grand Ballon is the apex of the Vosges Mountains, located 25 kilometres northwest of Mulhouse, France. It is also the highest point of the Alsace French region.

chateau-de-kaysersberg.title: Château de Kaysersberg
chateau-de-kaysersberg.description: The Château de Kaysersberg is a ruined castle in the commune of Kaysersberg in the Haut-Rhin département of France. It had an important strategic role as it allowed the Empire to close off one of the routes across the Vosges Mountains towards Lorraine. According to archaeological excavations and studies, the castle was abandoned at the end of the 16th century.

chateau-de-ferrette.title: Château de Ferrette
chateau-de-ferrette.description: The Château de Ferrette is a ruined castle in the commune of Ferrette in the Haut-Rhin département of France, built on the ruins of what was an observation tower built by the Romans

obernai.title: Obernai
obernai.description: Obernai is an important center of wine and beer production as well as a touristic destination. The historical wine of the city is called the Vin du Pistolet in reference to a local legend.

parent.title: Alsace
parent.description: See stunning views of castles, lakes, vineyards and towers in the Alsace region of northeastern France. Imagery collected by RésOT Alsace.
